There are a total of 47 accounting years of revenue expenditure (State Level-30-2 Heavy Expenditure, Local Level-15) under the 2403-Question (Compulsory) of the Department of Animal Husbandry under the Commissioner of Animal Husbandry. In order to expand the scope of facilities provided by the Department of Animal Husbandry and to make them more people-oriented by increasing their quality, to upgrade the quality of veterinary clinics, etc., institutions / offices / new ones under the Department have been created.

The posts of officers / staff working under the schemes implemented by the districts / as well as the department have been sanctioned from time to time, increased and adjusted by restructuring the posts as per the requirement.

The approval of a new sub-account title in each case for the rank is causing an unnecessary increase in the performance. Hence, there is undue delay in the payment of salary, non-salaried, and non-salaried accounts for the aforesaid headings.

It has been brought to the notice of the government that there are difficulties in meeting the prescribed time frame. In view of this, a proposal was under consideration of the Government to consolidate the various heads of accounts of compulsory expenditure under Demand No. D-4, Head of Accounts 2403 - Animal Husbandry.

Government Decision: - Demand No. D-4, Head of Accounts, Department of Animal Husbandry 2403 - To combine 16 head of accounts with 5 head of accounts for a total of 32 state level (30 + 2 weightage) headings on the state level of compulsory expenditure under animal husbandry. Also, out of a total of 15 titles at the local level, 12 titles were consolidated into 2.
